{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Coding Standards",
  "description": "Internal IPA code quality review using domain-segmented AI analysis (SEQUENTIAL execution for reliability). CRITICAL: Always loads project-specific standards AND passes them to subagents. Subagents explicitly load steering files for standards AND save files directly using fsWrite. Main agent NEVER reads intermediate files - Python handles all data loading. Step 14 uses plain text (not userInput) to ensure hooks execute on next message. Analyzes one domain at a time (Naming, JavaScript, SQL, Error Handling, Structure). Generates ONE Excel report per process with 4 sheets: Executive Dashboard, Enhanced Action Items, Detailed Analysis, and Process Flow diagram.",
  "version": "41",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "newSession": true,
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "IPA Coding Standards Review - Domain-Segmented Analysis\n\nThis is an INTERNAL code quality review, NOT client-facing documentation.\n\nCRITICAL: Analyze ONE process at a time using domain-segmented approach.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nARCHITECTURE: Domain-Segmented AI Analysis\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nProblem Solved: Context overload when analyzing large IPAs (500+ activities)\n\nSolution: Multi-pass AI analysis\n- Python organizes data by domain (5 small files vs 1 large file)\n- AI analyzes each domain separately (SEQUENTIAL for reliability)\n- Subagents save files directly using fsWrite (no main agent collection)\n- Python merges violations into master file\n- ONE Excel report generated\n\nDomains:\n1. Naming - Filenames, node captions, config sets\n2. JavaScript - ES5 compliance, performance, function order\n3. SQL - Queries, pagination, Compass SQL\n4. Error Handling - OnError tabs, GetWorkUnitErrors\n5. Structure - Process type, auto-restart, activity counts\n\nPython Role: Extract, organize, aggregate, format\nAI Role: Interpret standards, determine violations, assign severity, recommend\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nWORKFLOW - FOLLOW EXACTLY\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nSTEP 0: CLEAN TEMP FOLDER (AUTOMATIC - NO USER PROMPT)\n\nExecute PowerShell command to wipe Temp folder:\nRemove-Item Temp/* -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n\nThis ensures clean slate and prevents IDE indexing issues from accumulated files.\n\nMonitor workspace size:\n$tempFiles = (Get-ChildItem Temp -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object).Count\n$tempSize = [math]::Round((Get-ChildItem Temp -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object -Property Length -Sum).Sum / 1MB, 2)\n\nShow: \"📊 Workspace Status: Temp has $tempFiles files ($tempSize MB)\"\n\nIf ($tempFiles -gt 50 -or $tempSize -gt 100) {\n    Show warning: \"⚠️ Temp folder is large despite cleanup.\"\n}\n\nSTEP 1-4: USER SELECTION (Interactive)\n   1. List clients in Projects/ → User selects\n   2. List RICE items → User selects\n   3. List *.lpd files → User selects ONE\n   4. Confirm selection → User confirms\n\nSTEP 5: LOAD STEERING FILES\n   \n   readMultipleFiles([\n       '.kiro/steering/01_IPA_and_IPD_Complete_Guide.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/02_Work_Unit_Analysis.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/03_Process_Patterns_Library.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/05_Compass_SQL_CheatSheet.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/10_IPA_Report_Generation.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/11_RICE_Methodology_and_Specifications.md'\n   ])\n\nSTEP 6: LOAD PROJECT STANDARDS (REQUIRED)\n   \n   CRITICAL: Always execute this step - project standards override steering defaults\n   \n   Check: Projects/<Client>/project_standards_<Client>.xlsx\n   \n   If exists:\n      executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/excel_reader.py Projects/<Client>/project_standards_<Client>.xlsx --sheet Standards --json Temp/<Client>_standards.json\")\n      readFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\n      \n      Store standards in memory - will be passed to subagents\n   \n   If not exists:\n      Create empty standards file: fsWrite('Temp/<Client>_standards.json', '[]')\n      Subagents will use steering file defaults only\n\nSTEP 7: EXTRACT DATA (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_lpd_data import extract_lpd_data; extract_lpd_data(['<lpd_path>'], 'Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json')\\\"\")\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json\")\n\nSTEP 8: ORGANIZE BY DOMAIN (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_CodingStandards/organize_by_domain.py Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n   \n   Creates 5 domain files:\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_naming.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_javascript.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_sql.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_errorhandling.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_structure.json\n\nSTEP 9: LAUNCH DOMAIN ANALYZERS (SEQUENTIAL EXECUTION)\n   \n   Show: \"→ Step 9/14: Launching 5 analyzers sequentially...\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 1/5: Naming\n   \n   Show: \"→ Analyzer 1/5: Naming conventions...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-naming-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/10_IPA_Report_Generation.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze naming domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_naming.json\\n\\nCheck the process_type field to determine correct filename format:\\n- Approval Workflow → <Prefix>_WF_<Desc>.lpd\\n- Interface Process → <Prefix>_INT_<Source>_<Dest>_<Desc>.lpd\\n- Scheduled Process → <Prefix>_SCH_<Desc>.lpd\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nSTEP 4: Save violations\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_naming.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening bracket `[` and ending with `]`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing naming conventions\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"✓ Analyzer 1/5 complete: Naming\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 2/5: JavaScript\n   \n   Show: \"→ Analyzer 2/5: JavaScript ES5 compliance...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-javascript-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/01_IPA_and_IPD_Complete_Guide.md', '.kiro/steering/02_Work_Unit_Analysis.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze JavaScript domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_javascript.json\\n\\nAnalyze against ES5 compliance and performance standards.\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nSTEP 4: Save violations\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_javascript.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening bracket `[` and ending with `]`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing JavaScript ES5 compliance\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"✓ Analyzer 2/5 complete: JavaScript\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 3/5: SQL\n   \n   Show: \"→ Analyzer 3/5: SQL queries...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-sql-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/05_Compass_SQL_CheatSheet.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze SQL domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_sql.json\\n\\nAnalyze against Compass SQL and performance standards.\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nSTEP 4: Save violations\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_sql.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening bracket `[` and ending with `]`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing SQL queries\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"✓ Analyzer 3/5 complete: SQL\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 4/5: Error Handling\n   \n   Show: \"→ Analyzer 4/5: Error handling...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-error-handling-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/02_Work_Unit_Analysis.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze error handling domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_errorhandling.json\\n\\nAnalyze error handling coverage and OnError tabs.\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nSTEP 4: Save violations\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_errorhandling.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening bracket `[` and ending with `]`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing error handling coverage\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"✓ Analyzer 4/5 complete: Error Handling\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 5/5: Structure\n   \n   Show: \"→ Analyzer 5/5: Process structure...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-structure-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/01_IPA_and_IPD_Complete_Guide.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze structure domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_structure.json\\n\\nAnalyze auto-restart configuration and process structure.\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nSTEP 4: Save violations\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_structure.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening bracket `[` and ending with `]`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing process structure\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"✓ Analyzer 5/5 complete: Structure\"\n   Show: \"✓ All 5 analyzers complete\"\n   \n   IMPORTANT: Sequential execution prevents resource exhaustion.\n   Each subagent saves its own output file directly using fsWrite().\n\nSTEP 10: VERIFY SUBAGENT OUTPUTS\n   \n   CRITICAL: DO NOT READ SUBAGENT OUTPUTS - Python merges all data automatically\n   \n   Verify all files were saved by subagents (Test-Path only, DO NOT READ):\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_naming.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_javascript.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_sql.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_errorhandling.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_structure.json\")\n   \n   If any file is missing, STOP and report error.\n   DO NOT READ the files - they will be merged by Python in Step 11.\n\nSTEP 11: MERGE VIOLATIONS (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_CodingStandards/merge_violations.py Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n   \n   Creates: Temp/<ProcessName>_master_violations.json\n\nSTEP 12: CONFIRM REPORT GENERATION (AI)\n   \n   CRITICAL: DO NOT READ MASTER VIOLATIONS OR LPD DATA - Python tool handles all data loading\n   \n   Show summary of what was processed:\n   - Client: <Client>\n   - RICE Item: <RICE>\n   - Process: <ProcessName>\n   - Domains analyzed: Naming, JavaScript, SQL, Error Handling, Structure\n   \n   Ask: \"Generate coding standards report with this analysis?\"\n   WAIT for user confirmation\n   \n   NOTE: The build_ipa_data_helper.py tool will:\n   - Load master violations automatically\n   - Load LPD data automatically\n   - Build ipa_data structure\n   - Call template with proper format\n   - Handle all data processing\n\nSTEP 13: GENERATE REPORT (Python)\n   \n   Use build_ipa_data_helper.py and enhanced template\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Coding_Standards_Results/<Client>_<RICE>_CodingStandards_*.xlsx\")\n\nSTEP 14: ASK ABOUT NEXT PROCESS\n   \n   Show summary\n   Ask in plain text: \"Would you like to analyze another LPD file in this RICE item?\"\n   \n   CRITICAL: Do NOT use userInput tool - plain text allows hook execution\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nCRITICAL RULES\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n1. ONE PROCESS AT A TIME - 1:1 mapping: ONE LPD → ONE report\n\n2. DOMAIN-SEGMENTED ANALYSIS (SEQUENTIAL)\n   - Launch 5 specialized subagents ONE AT A TIME (Step 9)\n   - Sequential execution prevents resource exhaustion\n   - Each subagent loads project standards FIRST, then steering files\n   - Each subagent saves files directly using fsWrite (no main agent collection)\n   - Project standards override steering defaults\n\n3. MAIN AGENT NEVER READS INTERMEDIATE FILES\n   - Step 10: Verify files exist (Test-Path only, DO NOT READ)\n   - Step 12: Show summary only (DO NOT READ master violations or lpd data)\n   - Python tools handle ALL data loading and processing\n\n4. VIOLATIONS ONLY - Detailed Analysis sheet shows ONLY violations\n\n5. PYTHON LIFTS HEAVY LOAD - Python: Extract, organize, aggregate, format\n\n6. ONE EXCEL REPORT - 4 sheets: Executive Dashboard, Action Items, Detailed Analysis, Process Flow\n\n7. PROJECT STANDARDS PRECEDENCE\n   - Step 6: ALWAYS load project standards (required)\n   - Step 9: Subagents load project standards FIRST\n   - Project standards override steering file defaults\n\nPERFORMANCE:\n- Extraction: ~1s\n- Organization: ~2s\n- AI analysis (5 subagents sequential): ~2-3 min\n- Report generation: <10s\n- Total: ~2-3 min per process\n\nSUBAGENTS:\n- ipa-naming-analyzer: Filenames, captions, config sets\n- ipa-javascript-analyzer: ES5 compliance, performance\n- ipa-sql-analyzer: Compass SQL, pagination\n- ipa-error-handling-analyzer: OnError tabs, coverage\n- ipa-structure-analyzer: Auto-restart, process type"
  }
}